INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1326,'paper-74','Between-sample dynamics dynamics tests specify: (1) sample points, (2) bridge artifact, (3) actual dynamics, (4) error norm, (5) dynamics test verdict.','D','CrystalLib','claims','f30895c0184ddf5ceb695cc41309330f944a00f5cc0dc44161589fd89803f835');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1327,'paper-74','The meta-test error norm is the second derivative of the KL divergence with respect to the sample size, measured in units of the natural unit κ.','D','CrystalLib','claims','49a10a45ed1485e17e8f3aff38b3f3e2f1493ae4ebfa7d032351c42796b23512');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1328,'paper-74','Cross-validation is the meta-test procedure: the data is split into training and validation sets, and the validation is performed on the held-out set. The cross-validation error is the meta-test error.','D','CrystalLib','claims','f7b3cda80b24232f2728413c22b4f58713a9b5fd87f3a1daac3bc519f9a36910');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1329,'paper-74','Meta-calibration is the cross-validation of the calibration: the calibration is validated by holding out a subset of the data, calibrating on the remaining data, and testing on the held-out subset. The cross-validation error is the meta-calibration error.','D','CrystalLib','claims','137bcc6f67b6ae30a403d9e433925d5973c129f16c9ead783f5fbd9381e2ee3e');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1330,'paper-74','Standard reference materials (Paper 71, Corollary 1.5.1) are the cross-validation anchors: the PDG data sets are the held-out sets that the meta-calibration tests against.','D','CrystalLib','claims','43bd5c78882118bea7a580b20552bd20171f7ebdde5308cf7de97400877b9a51');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1331,'paper-74','Calibration consistency is cross-validation stability: the calibration is consistent if the cross-validation error is stable across different folds.','I','CrystalLib','claims','11e15ea6efac96b0edfc03b146c65c9ee387be06b67dae4fe9588e33f1b16d04');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1332,'paper-74','The meta-test is the boundary repair (Paper 5) of the test process: it removes the test boundary (noise, systematics) and validates the validation. The repair curvature is the meta-test error norm.','I','CrystalLib','claims','6ab52ff7dd210736dcd55e4e16d6f4a751bcb2bfed8fa2d2852ef756770e8c01');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1333,'paper-74','The meta-test is the receipt (Paper 11) of the validation process: it is a verifiable record that the validation is correct.','I','CrystalLib','claims','50f4f3a847b150eac16889d4b53f6fe53c089fb1fd32ccb3a6b907ff0e44c357');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1334,'paper-74','Boundary repair (Paper 5) ensures calibration integrity: the meta-test is the boundary repair of the test boundary, and the repair curvature is the meta-test error. The calibration is integrity-preserving if the repair curvature is below the threshold.','I','CrystalLib','claims','c4bf334147526be007ec48688aa45bf8e896b83484a7167a1375ff9839f05546');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1335,'paper-74','The lattice code chain 1→3→7→8→24→72 (Paper 4) provides the meta-level hierarchy: 1 meta-test, 3 test categories, 7 test criteria, 8 test protocols, 24 test cases, and 72 test runs.','I','CrystalLib','claims','1ef3f0805c62ec6215b031e7e3116439088757f76a712ae2fec368c6969de42f');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1336,'paper-74','The 72 E6 roots (Paper 91) are the test runs: each root corresponds to an independent test run that validates one degree of freedom of the LCR substrate. The Niemeier glue Γ₇₂ glues these runs into the unified test suite.','I','CrystalLib','claims','9f978dd7fc913be0b5c6e289148e4ec6b4d613196d9239f8972d8802827326b4');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1337,'paper-74','The LCR standards (Paper 39) ensure calibration consistency: the standards are the reference against which the meta-test is evaluated, and the calibration is consistent if it satisfies the standards.','I','CrystalLib','claims','784ff015fe8bf6699f722b70dded6e1cf4dcb1ea9fc717d744c38ec49d179210');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1338,'paper-74','The standards are the pass/fail thresholds for the meta-test: the calibration passes if it satisfies the standards; it fails otherwise.','I','CrystalLib','claims','a2aee65a620cc32b286ed78f5005dbd76b2b967e40c484a3779ada8d63260f6f');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1339,'paper-74','The cosmological framework (Paper 100) provides the capstone validation: the Big Bang = Higgs observing itself is the ultimate meta-test, and the calibration is consistent if it satisfies the cosmological framework.','I','CrystalLib','claims','d7d65b289e29b10ae1ced998e733c5832ee0f342af3250d8f667b6d54825d7a4');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(1340,'paper-74','The VOA weight assignment (Paper 16) anchors the pass/fail thresholds: w = 5 (Higgs) is the pass threshold, and w = 0 (vacuum) is the fail threshold.','I','CrystalLib','claims','bdd00fd500a30f5a891b92d1fc0d34ea5ce665b5b6fceb66ef61430bb8ff91b4');
