INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(2205,'paper-15','Claim 15.7. The chart carries eight states, not nine. The apparent `+1` is a dual reading of one state through the wrap (antipodal / Cayley-Dickson conjugation), not a separate ninth state: one gluon shows a color face or a white face depending on traversal. The wrap is a fixed-point-free involution, so the singlet axis is one state with two definite faces. This is the framework''s confinement reading: there is no colorless ninth gluon because there is no ninth state.','D','CrystalLib','claims','40fe8bef52066e0ae82231bd5bad8819a410f5d63079f9ec4751141b03ae4193');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(2206,'paper-15','Claim 15.8. The ninth slot is the forced printout (parity/trace) of the completed eight. It is genuinely neutral/superposed while the eighth slot is open, and is forced to exactly one of two values the instant the eighth slot fills. Superposition is therefore real but *transient*: the ninth is the Event-Law receipt of the eight (the master-receipt slot, Paper 10), not an independent state.','D','CrystalLib','claims','2065ffa0260a11a8397481204212a10d0af05c57f31c2a23e9ca20dce88fd398');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(2207,'paper-15','Claim 15.9. The nonstandard framework mass spectrum is a basis difference, not a failure. The chart `2^3 = 8` is the traceless `SU(3)` adjoint; the standard `3 x 3 = 9 = 8 (+) 1` (`3 (x) 3bar = adjoint (+) singlet`) carries the extra trace/singlet. The earlier honest non-match against the gauge-boson spectrum (Paper 13 Standard-Model comparison) is resolved as a `2x2x2` vs `3x3` reading-ordering difference; both readings are correct in their own basis.','D','CrystalLib','claims','cf1ec5bf4fa6ef1d01f69dadbea56ff248f6f757ec74cdc7f559e7cd6f77141d');
