INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3053,'paper-96','The finite game lattices (Paper 23) provide the game-theoretic model for the superpermutation: the superpermutation is the winning strategy of a finite game on the permutation lattice.','I','PaperLib','claims','dcf4b0b53fb6cae2029e4729dee3be71a17a6d41761cbb03194bd9aa78a948f8');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3054,'paper-96','The P vs NP problem (Paper 88) provides the complexity context: the superpermutation minimality is a special case of the combinatorial optimization problem.','I','PaperLib','claims','09365014a44092dcc242a9ba8e6cfee30cdbf5d0ae33672e54bdab0b66042892');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3055,'paper-96','The n=4 case gives minimal length 33; the n=5 case gives minimal length 153. Both are closed-now.','D','PaperLib','claims','5ca1feb54293272faa6a335a6b037bf037cb5209e5ff98d43a9b1bc0bb74f3ac');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3056,'paper-96','The n=4 case corresponds to the chain element 24 (the 24 permutations of 4 symbols); the n=5 case corresponds to the chain element 72 (the 72 automorphisms of the E6 root system, Paper 91).','I','PaperLib','claims','cf1e409dbe51f8da52d171571e17ef39c70e6edd8ee706ede5139c961781132c');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3057,'paper-96','The n=6, 7, 8 cases are open. The n=6 upper bound is 872; the lower bound is 864.','D','PaperLib','claims','6c67421229b60326a8e09acf085b4ee026acc7f23386e5c6e97c8d91b47975c5');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3058,'paper-96','The n=6 case requires the next element in the lattice code chain after 72. The next element is not yet defined.','I','PaperLib','claims','5ac694eb2df669d0cc3a2c432d39be17630c0104fe4609808fc84f82942c83c0');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3059,'paper-96','The superpermutation is the boundary repair (Paper 5) of the permutation boundary: the set of all n! permutations is a typed boundary, and the superpermutation is the minimal repair that connects all permutations into a single string.','I','PaperLib','claims','8627df4c7085d53c9306c07c3c15abeb990f1c1897922cf79395985bead62655');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3060,'paper-96','The superpermutation is the bridge artifact (Paper 8) between the discrete set of permutations and the continuous string of symbols.','I','PaperLib','claims','dd2543b1fa79148f93e7ba508e074d9f40957335a588c947ed79994eaee468e1');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3061,'paper-96','The LCR finite presentation (Paper 23) provides a model for the superpermutation minimality: the finite presentation is the set of generators and relations that define the permutation lattice, and the superpermutation is the minimal word that visits all generators.','I','PaperLib','claims','ac477c9d039e49f56f94ea7f271912463d18c828539114935022258a91ebd1af');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3062,'paper-96','The lattice code chain (Paper 4) is the presentation hierarchy: the chain elements are the generators of the finite presentation, and the superpermutation is the word that visits all generators in order.','I','PaperLib','claims','a84c29a5215d45ef248613fd8598492fb83142af0bbc5c27b0aed8ff99914995');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3063,'paper-96','The cosmological framework (Paper 100) is the cosmological superpermutation: the universe''s history is the superpermutation of all possible states, and the minimal length is the age of the universe.','I','PaperLib','claims','584ac0bde4c396a73db46c8d6e8fd071867f7e8d5a50363975bd8fd07b1867b0');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3064,'paper-96','The Monster VOA (Paper 18) encodes the superpermutation states. The McKay–Thompson coefficients c_n (Paper 90) are the number of distinct superpermutations at each length.','I','PaperLib','claims','ebb5fbf41347d4100dae90c816691cf6f51bfae468cc475d2d7879daa236e301');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3065,'paper-96','The minimal superpermutation is the Monster VOA state with the lowest non-zero weight that contains all permutations as sub-states.','I','PaperLib','claims','7728975aee2be2b18a7b34aa487623de206001c80f29ea08fedf3c297e1a8b4b');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3066,'paper-96','2 SM mapping rows claimed for LCR-96; the backing file does not exist.','X','PaperLib','claims','ed452ca94c7507695af141f71dc11a496820781a259bbd5e41d72f646711549b');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3067,'paper-97','The EHX accounting tracks the electron, hole, recombination, screening, and exciton states. The accounting is the standard physics import that explains part of the open math.','D','PaperLib','claims','55463541da0f49f241a5c1acdf1f0e2a232e5b0eb93d31c7c34b02eb99372da0');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3068,'paper-97','The exciton states are classified by the quantum numbers n, l, m and spin. The 1s exciton is the ground state; the 2s, 2p, 3s, 3p, 3d, 4s are the excited states.','D','PaperLib','claims','91fe2043b5b6d379be95b4a8aa294947ad0a408e036d05168e2cebdfcb65ba9b');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3069,'paper-97','The energy accounting is the conservation of energy in the EHX system: the total energy E = E_e + E_h + E_X + E_screen is conserved.','D','PaperLib','claims','21e1f998fefc1c1697f4828dbae04514659a0c58e37be4a6c0b5ec95f24d1bc5');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3070,'paper-97','The entropy balance is the extension of the EHX accounting to thermodynamics: the entropy production is the recombination rate, and the entropy flow is the energy transport across the EHX boundary.','D','PaperLib','claims','5458df7a7658c33f000a5ab382d2b5fb137e479f72da7b68e5d0f9fc35366d5d');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3071,'paper-97','The exergy is the useful work extracted from the EHX system: the exergy E_x = E − T_0 S is the maximum work that can be extracted at temperature T_0.','D','PaperLib','claims','d116fd7862f7416f1436d454d8044747b77c6879539221024efd6e2232f7b964');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3072,'paper-97','The mass residue (Paper 16) is the exergy anchor: the exciton binding energy E_b is the exergy of the electron-hole pair, and the VOA weight assignment anchors the exergy at the Higgs scale.','I','PaperLib','claims','4c9b716d663a323ff4ac6c062a92e38ce4b8895c56e452cecc2c573db701b7fc');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3073,'paper-97','The deep dive is the explicit application of the EHX accounting to the open math: many of the "open" obligations are well-understood in terms of standard EHX physics.','I','PaperLib','claims','07c796169a898eda53e6e9f88e46b4d098997490dfc527d0966ba2588a60be6b');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3074,'paper-97','The open math obligations are the boundary (Paper 5) between the derived and the underived parts of the LCR framework. The EHX accounting is the repair that removes this boundary by importing the standard physics.','I','PaperLib','claims','bf2d4be9782fb41ac96726624381688ae496b9375f48a9ddec8bd823d331d0cc');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3075,'paper-97','The lattice code chain 1→3→7→8→24→72 (Paper 4) underlies the EHX structure: 1 = electron, 3 = hole states, 7 = exciton states, 8 = spin-charge combinations, 24 = exciton states (including spin and valley), 72 = electron-hole pairs (E6 roots, Paper 91).','I','PaperLib','claims','444ed532f176df2722402964c6ad99e607e63c8028fe93482b5e893770bfe510');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3076,'paper-97','The 72 E6 roots (Paper 91) are the 72 electron-hole pairs: each root corresponds to a distinct electron-hole configuration. The Niemeier glue Γ₇₂ glues the electron and hole into the exciton.','I','PaperLib','claims','3fdf4c28753b9d35c5b3250c03653a8b9a283d411e4ec55efa597997cf437227');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3077,'paper-97','The VOA weight assignment (Paper 16) anchors the exciton binding energy. The binding energy E_b = κ²/(2μ) · 10⁻⁹, where κ = 25.05 GeV is the natural unit and 10⁻⁹ is the solid-state suppression scale.','I','PaperLib','claims','7778a63fad4151451a2bd6733c36b973438b01f49439e8de49930a5b1d130634');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3078,'paper-97','The VOA weight assignment is the exergy anchor: the exciton binding energy is the exergy of the electron-hole pair, and the VOA weight gives the scale of the exergy.','I','PaperLib','claims','12352b9c693e4fb8f2eb9053aeca5b391456442df4cfe83c20142bf7833d3fd9');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3079,'paper-97','The cosmological framework (Paper 100) is the ultimate energy balance: the Big Bang = Higgs observing itself is the initial energy state, and the EHX accounting is the local realization of the cosmological energy balance.','I','PaperLib','claims','70aa5c79a8d3d77d48384c9fe54c2f239801407ec53cb298a36bce07ac116cf4');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3080,'paper-97','The capstone (Paper 100) validates the exergy analysis: the exergy of the EHX system is the local measure of the cosmological energy available for work.','I','PaperLib','claims','04703e72aecc6e33a7ee238e3920ccb692310646f9937de2420102bd0a071c17');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3081,'paper-97','The Monster VOA (Paper 18) encodes the many-body EHX states. The McKay–Thompson coefficients c_n (Paper 90) are the degeneracies of the n-electron-hole configuration: c_n counts the number of ways to arrange n electrons and holes in the EHX lattice.','I','PaperLib','claims','5507376ce30e155da3f212ee99123c600b45b50785dd203084e50e1fdb993d07');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3082,'paper-97','The EHX accounting is a subspace of the Monster VOA: the electron, hole, and exciton states are the low-weight states of the VOA. The exciton binding energy corresponds to the VOA weight w = 1.','I','PaperLib','claims','c71e6c878fc75d20ba9d6d8a48df7eda3dfd708a054367a2624fb6afe74c9277');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3083,'paper-97','2 SM mapping rows claimed for LCR-97; the backing file does not exist.','X','PaperLib','claims','342f71c65f70d5ca2cffb283ecf7c31ddb870ad40a5532ff8f466bba3b80761e');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3084,'paper-98','The reasoned reapplication is the cross-domain closure table: the standard math, physics, CS, numerical analysis, and formal-methods knowledge is applied before any claim is called residual.','I','PaperLib','claims','4b933ce6113a9257dba16482ac4a458cda2ce11924e9d045f37edcf922b318fa');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3085,'paper-98','The cross-domain closure table is the lattice closure (Paper 9) across the domains: the table must close under the intersection of all domains, meaning every claim is verified by at least one domain.','I','PaperLib','claims','625a49d0d03c7ec482968c3185b54c15be8008b81f7ccfa669a0c8bd5dc38a9c');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3086,'paper-98','Knowledge reuse is the reapplication of standard formalism: the knowledge stored in one domain is reapplied to another domain when the domains share a common structure.','I','PaperLib','claims','be0778ccc8cb360607a0be15a3d0445c1aee290c7ef8f4ff2e7f28d8a70bf681');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3087,'paper-98','Analogical reasoning is the cross-domain mapping: the analogy between two domains is the map that preserves the structure, and the reapplication is the transfer of knowledge along this map.','D','PaperLib','claims','a16ea505b2f1230b96aba007619ca3d940dc25309e14991a2935f583f8a330ec');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3088,'paper-98','Transfer learning is the domain adaptation: the knowledge learned in one domain is transferred to another domain by adapting the model to the new domain''s data. The LCR receipt structure enables this transfer by recording the knowledge in a domain-independent form.','D','PaperLib','claims','eae47d3d5e8367af6dcf0a852c93fbc5f0d81c5ee3651666fb8e48e57971b3e4');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3089,'paper-98','The CAM crystal projectors (Paper 28) are the knowledge store: the projectors store the standard formalism in a form that can be reapplied across domains.','I','PaperLib','claims','2e243367a8565ec2988948e02c80b3f73234fb7fd0264a7729280ef721f19f44');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3090,'paper-98','The corpus ribbon (Paper 29) is the transfer learning sequence: the ribbon is the sequence of knowledge applications across domains, and each segment of the ribbon is a transfer learning step.','I','PaperLib','claims','4735398f0ea2b468d2d572eed5459645caba77c37ab4a4564c4c3fafcce8552d');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3091,'paper-98','The non-explained remainder is the open obligation: the part of the open math that is not explained by the standard formalism.','I','PaperLib','claims','d17538f5abc781315c94844164c89dfb6280ccef9c3729dff5fb5f6046891781');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3092,'paper-98','The non-explained remainder is the boundary (Paper 5) between the standard formalism and the open math. The boundary repair is the future research that will close the gap.','I','PaperLib','claims','524544dd641deb992f6ddacfad1ab58fc99ee680c4452a8aa3ab74722119eee3');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3093,'paper-98','The lattice code chain 1→3→7→8→24→72 (Paper 4) underlies the domain hierarchy: 1 = mathematics, 3 = physics, 7 = computer science, 8 = numerical analysis, 24 = formal methods, 72 = open math.','I','PaperLib','claims','b15432661b9a5b5495538fbbe464ddae9d857f125d0c412878d4d715b36bc9ca');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3094,'paper-98','The 72 E6 roots (Paper 91) are the 72 open problems: each root corresponds to an open problem in the cross-domain table. The Niemeier glue Γ₇₂ glues these problems into the unified open-math lattice.','I','PaperLib','claims','dc8472a0e21eac1d787e590b3ed159797c194322ce0e7a90bf3297fb3e6c3011');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3095,'paper-98','The VOA weight assignment (Paper 16) anchors the "weight" of each domain: mathematics w=1, physics w=3, computer science w=7, numerical analysis w=8, formal methods w=24, open math w=72.','I','PaperLib','claims','ab901add0f0449e4a5c715c52fc70d9fc754a4d6db860673963ff76db87d32cc');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3096,'paper-98','The LCR receipt structure (Paper 11) enables reasoned reapplication: the receipts record the knowledge in a domain-independent form, and the reapplication is the replay of the receipts in a new domain.','I','PaperLib','claims','3cbb74f91975cabbee496660c4c19921423821d991b97219be242e05091f8bbb');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3097,'paper-98','The receipt replay is the knowledge transfer: the replay of a receipt from one domain to another is the transfer of knowledge along the receipt chain.','I','PaperLib','claims','31fc4a7d0c285bbd8af1858f74fbbff04a5876d86b1a982978452b5dfb4c1d7d');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3098,'paper-98','The cosmological framework (Paper 100) is the ultimate closure: the capstone closes all domains by providing the cosmological context that unifies them.','I','PaperLib','claims','abf38171ea59675ac4f0f22b463bb6d201df44b8ce33534c94bd2967b5ec569f');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3099,'paper-98','The Monster VOA (Paper 18) encodes the universal closure table. The McKay–Thompson coefficients c_n (Paper 90) are the number of closure relations at level n: c_n counts the number of verified claims that have weight n.','I','PaperLib','claims','5a1b81ddad9e84d5450443806b52a4a58d477bc2bd3090fc9dd051c9cecd9227');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3100,'paper-98','The cross-domain closure table is a subspace of the Monster VOA: the verified claims are the low-weight states, and the open problems are the high-weight states.','I','PaperLib','claims','16b9ad44bb2a0f00cbf22818b5a55f69ab0340ba2bf3e7a3e734859a53d47853');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3101,'paper-98','2 SM mapping rows claimed for LCR-98; the backing file does not exist.','X','PaperLib','claims','5a4e3205da8efb1821c6dab48669409071c0912b8301fdc6acd1844509ab9cdd');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3102,'paper-99','The applied forge validation is an open obligation (NP-07). The collection of real-world data is ongoing.','D','PaperLib','claims','89e2ef366d0921f13aee89738cc66c9b7dc457403e940ae552e91cae9668c525');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3103,'paper-99','The validation is the receipt stack replay: the forge''s predictions are replayed against experimental receipts to verify correctness.','I','PaperLib','claims','805a58f12f9a88ec72da75b4499ef4e391aab0e9d64a128ea14feee9be49f6de');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3104,'paper-99','End-to-end testing is the validation pipeline: the forge is tested from input (lattice code chain) to output (physical predictions).','I','PaperLib','claims','6c724ba8e5351cafb743a8536ae8fa743108dfcc2df1f75ff0df128f0a944786');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3105,'paper-99','Forge validation is the end-to-end verification of the LCR substrate: the forge reads the lattice code chain, produces physical predictions, and validation verifies predictions match real-world data.','I','PaperLib','claims','3a9092aea4786df194387f044fbb323a87af626e7d568438e5c0560045b14d7e');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3106,'paper-99','The Grand Reconstruction Map (Paper 40) is the validation blueprint.','I','PaperLib','claims','d06ceec5c62f3844d4dd34091078e81987c361827c00378e06c4237bbf484a73');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3107,'paper-99','Verification protocols are receipt standards: protocols define criteria for valid receipt, and validation verifies receipts meet criteria.','I','PaperLib','claims','1586c664bb5b86e3a2d27752f48dc26cf394c2b15dff37b742ff6fad276dcb90');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3108,'paper-99','The bounded validation is the closed-now substrate: the kernel is verified against the LCR substrate (Paper 20).','D','PaperLib','claims','e650a37cbcdf08282bfbeab67ab851c2598b8f9b0b3d04cb82e88b2b5e7a6544');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3109,'paper-99','The bounded validation is the lattice closure (Paper 9) of the forge: every prediction reaches a terminal address.','I','PaperLib','claims','c83adfbda128d83ef4315a6ecb6eee1b88227c4a3ab58a97118da48f4cc3cb02');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3110,'paper-99','The lattice code chain 1→3→7→8→24→72 provides validation levels: 1 unit test, 3 integration tests, 7 system tests, 8 acceptance tests, 24 field tests, 72 real-world deployments.','I','PaperLib','claims','3da771ad40ac014457e48352456e58755e1e51ca253259f188bb5eaeb9dfbd20');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3111,'paper-99','The 72 E6 roots are the 72 real-world deployments; each root corresponds to a distinct experimental validation; the Niemeier glue Γ₇₂ glues deployments into the unified validation suite.','I','PaperLib','claims','a99d6d75834a6be1ce143efb2aa51ac067bcf265aaffb59b8a8be1aa52846f78');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3112,'paper-99','LCR standards (Paper 39) ensure forge validation consistency: standards are criteria the forge must satisfy.','I','PaperLib','claims','0d63b290bbaeb2ea399a729d750a547838e52a1fb8dcf3d0dfa2408e72153df7');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3113,'paper-99','The standards are pass/fail criteria for forge validation.','I','PaperLib','claims','758858b2d6f480479891e61d5c027b592db08425736ac9aab8f3d6c4f61922bb');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3114,'paper-99','The cosmological framework (Paper 100) is the ultimate validation: the forge is valid iff it satisfies the cosmological framework.','I','PaperLib','claims','03f5cce5fa876a4e940e77c9382d1a564b999e9b7d91dfcf0e7b6e6c01bcd96e');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3115,'paper-99','The VOA weight assignment (Paper 16) anchors validation metrics. The primary test case is Higgs mass m_H = 5κ = 125.25 GeV; forge must predict within error norm ε < 0.01.','D','PaperLib','claims','eccba859be744ba45b4d564aca82bf727b88e846362cbbd934afcda3cfc65293');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3116,'paper-99','All other validation metrics (top mass, Z mass, etc.) are mass residues (Paper 16) of the VOA weight assignment: predicted as integer multiples of κ.','D','PaperLib','claims','2a737ba3cf655addb70cd58778e7609509115d043013bb614a443733fa2a2606');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3117,'paper-99','The Monster VOA (Paper 18) encodes validation states. The McKay–Thompson coefficients c_n (Paper 90) count validated predictions at weight n.','I','PaperLib','claims','32bd0cccf8e25716a53156c13823265dcdffbbeddf884b3ff984d98024f68f88');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3118,'paper-99','Validated predictions are the low-weight states of the Monster VOA; unvalidated predictions are the high-weight states.','I','PaperLib','claims','fa6a9718572a284706a472f3d28c7a15a2cd764be1c705a37126cc8f68e27b37');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3119,'paper-99','In the LCR cosmological framework (Paper 100), validation is the "observation" of the forge by the real world: Big Bang = Higgs observing itself, and validation is the observation of the forge by the Higgs.','I','PaperLib','claims','0d2b9c654e059013821bbb739193a7f058205a54ab442e29e519d4b19ae33968');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3120,'paper-99','The capstone (Paper 100) is the ultimate forge validation: the cosmological framework validates the forge by requiring predictions consistent with Big Bang = Higgs observing itself.','I','PaperLib','claims','1194ede55b368c3e8160d4cb7ac340abfa4fcf433ec98f97726849d8a8f0b05e');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3121,'paper-99','The forge validation is the cosmological observation: the forge produces predictions, and validation is the observational confirmation.','I','PaperLib','claims','59f7d44ee343dffa525117865d7434dd8bfb062a1041beb5dce91c5a35990fdd');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3122,'paper-99','SM mapping file does not exist; 2 rows are inferred.','X','PaperLib','claims','a44ef1455ee938844cd113844925320613c0f49d09e88f59e05024718bb6148d');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3123,'paper-100','The 100-paper series spans 3 bands: A (1–30), B (31–39) + Paper 40, B′ (41–80), C (81–100). The destination is the 2-category ℒ (Paper 80); the bridge is the Grand Reconstruction Map (Paper 40).','D','PaperLib','claims','4296095a06639a9541a6318e21bfbdc220862ec94752045c80a548b2acb6dc39');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3124,'paper-100','The 3 bands are the 3 phases of the LCR framework: Band A = mathematical substrate ("language"), Band B/B′ = physical translation ("physics"), Band C = application ("proofs").','I','PaperLib','claims','ec28508928eee06578878d9b16d80a4d91ee310fe7dc3f9e9e5f048562bb982d');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3125,'paper-100','The 100 papers are the complete LCR framework: every paper contributes to ℒ, and every claim is backed by a receipt.','I','PaperLib','claims','4fd131328ffec2856584acbd210b9d1919c4b14a56dd19d70535e8d4e331af1f');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3126,'paper-100','The 2-category ℒ is the closed form of the LCR language. Objects are typed 5-tuples (L, C, R, Σ, ∂) (Paper 80).','D','PaperLib','claims','068439b20ecd846e8c42878d3a5cddfc7669f60b78f8228160a9db27e683ed2a');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3127,'paper-100','The 8 1-morphisms are the 8 admissible operations: lookup, repair, fold, terminal, ledger, window, bridge, admit.','D','PaperLib','claims','dfa139b1336fcfb04bbb3d0e11f7e99999f6c8baaa4d76495436880309aa4dae');
INSERT INTO "meta_claims" VALUES(3128,'paper-100','The 7 2-morphisms are the 7 claim-lane promotions.','D','PaperLib','claims','bb3184bbbcf76980862411d45bbbfee10ccdbe1ef651a57ee95ba5b0d3a9389a');
